      • deleteRuns

        public int deleteRuns(Recording recording,
                      java.util.List<KeplerLSID> lsids,
                      boolean authenticate)
               throws RecordingException,
                      AuthenticationException
        Delete runs in provenance and from local list. Also if this WRM is connected to a remote store, delete runs from tracker file *if* they have been imported (not simply a preview run) then call updatePreviewRuns to put the preview run(s) back in the system. Calls fireWorkflowRunManagerEvent to notify listeners.
        Parameters:
        recording -
        lsids -
        authenticate -
        Returns:
        int numRowsDeleted
        Throws:
        RecordingException
        AuthenticationException

        public int deleteRunsLocally(java.util.List<KeplerLSID> execLSIDs)
        Delete runs from local list, CacheManager, and ObjectManager, but not from provenance. Do this e.g. when removing an older version of a run, e.g. during the change of a run from running to complete.

      • getAssociatedWorkflowForWorkflowRun

        public ComponentEntity getAssociatedWorkflowForWorkflowRun(KeplerLSID runLSID)
        Return the ComponenteEntity that was run to create the WorkflowRun that is identified by the given LSID. This method first checks to see if there is an existing object in the ObjectManager (which also checks the CacheManager if no object is found in the ObjectManager). If no object is found in the ObjectManager and no new object is created from the CacheManager then this method checks the provenance database for the workflow and parses a new NamedObj from the moml string stored there.
        Parameters:
        runLSID -
        Returns:
